Priscilla Ediare, Ado-Ekiti Ekiti Government has confirmed three new cases of COVID-19. The results came in on Saturday night. According to the state’s COVID-19 update, it revealed that, “as at 9:00am today, May 10, there are 10 active cases of COVID-19 in Ekiti State. “It further revealed that two more have been discharged. This brings the total confirmed cases in the state to 15, of which 10 are active, four discharged and one death,” the government said in the update.